text: Chicabal crater lakeChicabal is a inactive volcano in the Quetzaltenango department of Guatemala. Its edifice has a volume of . The volcano has a crater lake, Chicabal Lake, and is constructed within a collapse scar that may have been the consequence of a failure of a previous edifice. It is associated with Santa Maria volcano. ==References== Category:Mountains of Guatemala Category:Subduction volcanoes Category:Stratovolcanoes of Guatemala Category:Quetzaltenango Department
